Package ORG.oclc.oai.server.catalog

Class Summary
AbstractCatalog AbstractCatalog is the generic interface between OAICat and any arbitrary database.
ExtendedJDBCOAICatalog ExtendedJDBCOAICatalog is an example of how to implement the AbstractCatalog interface for JDBC.
ExtendedJDBCRecordFactory ExtendedJDBCRecordFactory converts JDBC "items" to "record" Strings.
FileRecordFactory FileRecordFactory converts native XML "items" to "record" Strings.
FileSystemOAICatalog FileSystemOAICatalog is an implementation of AbstractCatalog interface with the data sitting in a directory on a filesystem.
IMSXMLRecordFactory IMSXMLRecordFactory converts native XML items to Record objects and vice versa.
JDBCLimitedOAICatalog JDBCLimitedOAICatalog is an example of how to implement the AbstractCatalog interface for JDBC.
JDBCOAICatalog JDBCOAICatalog is an example of how to implement the AbstractCatalog interface for JDBC.
JDBCRecordFactory JDBCRecordFactory converts JDBC "items" to "record" Strings.
NewFileRecordFactory NewFileRecordFactory converts native XML "items" to "record" Strings.
NewFileSystemOAICatalog NewFileSystemOAICatalog is an implementation of AbstractCatalog interface with the data sitting in a directory on a filesystem.
RecordFactory RecordFactory is responsible for pulling various pieces of information from native records such as the identifier, datestamp, and sets.
XMLFileOAICatalog XMLFileOAICatalog is an implementation of AbstractCatalog interface with the data sitting in a directory on a filesystem.
XMLFileRecordFactory XMLFileRecordFactory converts native XML "items" to "record" Strings.
XMLRecordFactory XMLRecordFactory converts native XML "items" to "record" Strings.
